se.jbee.inject
Interface Parameter<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
Argument, Dependency, Instance, Type
public interface Parameter<T>

Parameters are *not* about to find/identify the Constructor to use! This would get far to complex to understand (yet simple to implement) using different constructors depending on the Parameters. Parameters identify the Instance to use for the constructor specified or given by ConstructionStrategy!

How Parameters are understood:

A Class (via Type)
Use the default instance of the given Class
A Type
Use the default instance of the given Type (needed for generic classes)
An Instance
Use the instance identified by the given Instance
A Dependency
Use the instance resolved by the given Dependency (finest level of control)
An instance Object
Use the given Object (for the first parameter it is assignable to)

Jan Bernitt (jan.bernitt@gmx.de)
